Really nice roof jug haul.
Felt really hard, but I did it 2nd go. Soft.
Super softy, another flash courtesy of c Barthel beta. Very good looking line with great moves. Left hand crux hold is kinda uncomfortable tho
Super endurancy, fun weird climbing. With so many good holds and so many possible sequences height really doesn't matter
Pretty cool til your head hits the other rock.
Og non-cheaty beta feels like 10. When on tour...

And here I thought I wasn't going to recommend anything in Hueco... Sick steep juggy wall with a dyno and a contortiony kneebar make this long climb a real keeper. End of the day send train with Austin
Another super softy, but similar to rumble with a much harder crux at the end of the problem. My toehooking is definitely leveling up. Thought I wasn't gonna do it til I said last go and it was soft
I sincerely hope that's what happens after you die
Don't downgrade things because women can do them, downgrade them because they are soft
Cool movement, pretty brutal.
I do not have the endurance to be climbing bs like this. kind of cool for a dabby traverse. Definitely touched a crash pad.

Heinously hard definitely not v5. Got scared with no pads on the flash go, pulled back on and realized I do have balls, no matter how small they may be, and did the dyno, then sent from the start. Again, super hard for v5. Soft.
1st try after starpower, so 2nd go soft. Contrived.
Campused out of the pockets, felt heinous. Ice cream looks really hard. Rain and rest days on the horizon.

Tempted to log this as a route, but fanny doesn't rope climb. 20 ft of climbing to any of a variety of no hands kneebar rests, then another 20 ft of climbing. Definitely touched the ground at least twice in the middle. Hard for me.
Wtf super heinous. Also pretty cool.
Climbed the beginning well, then everything fell apart but I tried hard and made it. Cool weird moves!
Basically a route, 35 ft. Jug haul so good. No idea why I'm calling this soft it was really hard. Soft.
Took a few goes to stick the jump move, but the top is really easy with the knee bar. Feels solid in the grade, probably the standard for 11 in hueco. Soft.
Felt a bit easier than the other 10s today. Tried Loaded direct first, didn't fraish so I tried this next. That knee-bar is so cool...
Pretty cool minus the dropoff. Dor is close, did all the moves, it'll go first burn next time for sure!
Sick. Steep jug hauls are so fun.
Taking the onsight because I grabbed just about every hold wrong and downclimbed at least a move. Underclings... ewww. At least it's a drop off
3 tries. Easier than predator but I hate underclings.
Spray down from Tomer was an integral part of the Fraish. Still almost fell off at the very end, and the topout was kinda sketchy pumped!
Stick left foot up ass, do awkward move off underclings. Stick right foot up ass, bump again. So good.
This is a real v10. So sick.
Sharp shart
Difficult pinch move at the top. Got hailed on really hard today

Felt really hard but I basically campused the crux section so there is probably better softy beta. Almost fell off the topout. Really glad Dor got me this knee pad its getting some serious mileage out here!
Shoulda coulda woulda but didn't frash. 2nd go soft is good too!
So many super long roof climbs here I'm getting tired
Chuffed around at the top, almost fell.
Felt hard, but had no beta. Soft. Definitely going out on a whimper more so than a bang this trip.
Felt hard. No Right Martini today that's for sure.
Really difficult. Or maybe I'm just fat. Good thing there's a no hands kneebar rest, or I would definitely slide out of a Baby Martini jug.

Stage 2 warm up for swarm. If t bird is 11, this is 13, albeit low end. Hardest move for me is the easiest move for everyone else, only fell once on the t bird move. Best contrived dropoff I've climbed in a while.

I punted off this 6 years ago so I'll have to take the P Rob flash. Climbed it with the worst beta that exists, but there was such a long line to climb that I didn't want to let go. Nice way to round out a trip dub for the day. Lucid dreaming is next!!!

Psyched to finish this thing after punting off the last move in my first session. Thought for a moment I was going to take it to the top on the flash go after sticking the first 3 moves, but the shoulder move is still hard! Ended up sending first go of the 3rd session. Glad practicing all those ling drive by's finally paid off. Shout out to Jess and all the people who hiked/sledded out to support me!
Proud send train with Mark on the points day. Super fun times sun bathing and stacking with the crew!
Came back and did the very bottom move off the low low holds, might bump it to softy 11.

Been trying this forever, finally felt soft. My mortar breakthrough is at hand! 1st go today right after Go Go Gadget. Nemeses were dropping like it was hot today. Only took me 10 sessions so I'll dg.
So damn hard for me, sent first try of the sesh today! Keep laughing Will, keep laughing. 5 or 6 sessions, must be soft. Who's gonna do the sit?
Hell yes! Trip dubbed at Mortar how the hell did this happen. After the stand went sit only took a few tries. Mortar lvl up day.

Punted first session but managed to be part of the 2 3 4 train this time. Rad line, feels 11 ish if you avoid taking wing. Dor crushed all her projects today and the sandbox was sending hard too! Great day out in the valley.
4th go soft. Felt very easy for the grade but I need the pointzz
Tried as hard as I could, and consequently climbed it terribly. Good to see I'm stronger than I was 6 years ago. Hardest thing I did this weekend by at least 4 grades. Soft.
If Dream gets 10 this certainly gets at least as much. Zorro eliminate dyno, good times almost ripping my hand off! Perfect warmup.

3rd go soft. Kicked the tree on the flash go, wussed out from the top 2nd go, and realized it was soft 3rd go. Fairly standard progression for me. Mantle was scary until I did it, and then it too was soft.
Damn near perfect boulder, just tall enough, very cool movement, and a high heel lockoff well off the deck. Mega send train with the crew!
Crappy sharp difficult problem next to Armistice. Felt V10 to me until I started campusing most of it, then it felt like V9. Soft.
Pretty hard at the bottom, and the top is precarious. Just as hard as I remember it being in high school.

3rd go. After getting scared on Flatline I was not confident about going ground up on this one.  But then Dean came to us in the form of a Raven, and after taking a couple falls off the big move in the dying light I stuck it and reconnected with a headspace I thought I'd lost a long time ago. Actually felt pretty tame, psyched to get back to highballing!
Fun mantle. Should not have been on this in the sun. Felt like 7 from the sit, stand is the better problem though...
Sick one! Surprised I haven't been to it until now. Isamer finally sent harder than V5!
Pretty hard for soft 7. Did the FA of Squirrel direct and Squirrel Super Direct (AKA Squirrel Mantle) too. Ice fell off the last move and didn't send (classic).
Felt like it wasn't going to go and then Isamer got kind of close, and Bryce campused it, and then it felt soft.
4th go. Kind of almost fraished. Worst fraish day ever. Really cool reachy climb, hope everything stays reachy...
3rd go. Chris "Copperhead" Chen put in 3 sessions today to no avail. He'll be back for venganza!
1 hard V9 move into BS = Soft
Very cool climbing on great rock. Really good!

Wow what a really cool uncontrived climb with a pure sit start on comfortable, solid holds. NOT. Sit start at the crimps is wack and stupid (although easy), started at the sloper rail. Still contrived because the jugs out right are off. Also broke a hold on the send. Bryce has the rest...
Very cool line on heinously sharp and unattractive rock.
Another line with bad rock, but awesome movement on this one. Dyno to finish! Second go soft train with Bryce.
Super fun climb. Jugs to a super bump, pogo, or toehook lockoff depending on your preference.
The more obvious line next to Gandhi AKA Yogalates. Still didn't start on the crimps because they're sharp and it's dumb.
Very cool tufas at the start to face crimping. One of the best in the area.
This climb sums up the Flu for me, as it is at the top of the hill. The Flu has 2 star bouldering with 5 star trails. Only did this one because Kinder did. It was bad.

1st go, 3rd session in standard fashion. Then Bryce smashed his mega proj and I almost followed him up it. Nothing will ever be as easy as straight down pulling on crimps for me. Good thing Isamer left or I wouldn't have sent. Mega soft for me. Yatta!
Felt impossible for a long time, which makes sense because Chris crushed it. Finally realized it was soft when I death crimped through the pain.
I hate underclings. All I have left in Joe's is underclings. 4 or 5 sessions super soft.

First came up here with Bryce a year and a half ago, and couldn't do any of the moves. Wouldn't have come back to it if he wasn't so psyched, but slowly it came together. Watching him send got me amped to get it done, and even though I missed the send train I managed to Yatta it on my 4th session. So satisfying to hit the lip!

Harder than gentleman's, and quite similar, so soft 11 seems appropriate. Committed way too hard for a hold I wasn't sure was a jug and took a huge swing that would have landed me 5 feet off the pads if I hadn't held on. Definitely dabbed on Bryce a bit, but at that point it was do or die and I did so I'm counting it.
Glad I never have to do that first awful undercling move again. top of this problem has cool movement, albeit contrived movement...
Eww underclings
Chris and Bryce were here and they did climb today. Bryce almost flashed, and then didn't do it... Nooooo
4 sessions, finally figured out the beta and it was definitely soft. Surprised more people don't climb this classic test piece.
Felt really hard. Soft. Will you were definitely on the V3 not this one.
Hard for me. Once again had to skip all the holds to make it happen. Scrunchy underclings are my favorite. Blastoff!

3rd go. Approached up the wrong gully (classic map-less vague directions) and spent 3 hours finding this. Crux is always finding the boulder in Tahoe. At least it was really really soft! And cool. Would take 10 but all that hiking through manzanitas in shorts was miserable.
3rd go. Had to figure out the easiest beta for me. Softy softy so plush and soft.
Really wanted to take it but I just couldn't. So so so soft even at 10, really adds nothing to climb jugs to this one lock off.
Dor almost did it, but the heel hook was prohibitive... Tryna make consensus on some of these chossy boulders. This one is ok.
From the sit. Totally whaled at the top. If I was ever planning on coming back I would want a new topout sequence. Nice work Scotty!
From the sit. Cool climb, kind of chossy holds. Not sure what universe this gets V10 in but hey it's pretty fun! Nice punt Alan.
3rd go soft. Pretty cool, pretty soft. Might have to retro upgrade The Seam.

Decided to come here instead of Tahoe, and ended up sitting in bumper to bumper traffic for 4 hours and (not) sleeping in a mosquito infested marsh. At least I got to hang with Pinchy and watch him crush!

Went from being very scary to not so scary to soft. Looks like you'll fall in the pit, but you probably won't. Awesome climb, definitely one of the best in the valley, and somehow I had never heard of it. Billy with the punt!
Our generation, my generation, something like that. Sweet edge climbing takes you high of the deck to a glory jug topout. Pretty sure I tried this like 7 years ago but I'll take a P Rob 2nd go soft.

The dick was definitely soft. Super entertaining one mover for me, with a huge deadpoint off a heel to a sloper, at which point your hand cuts and you hold tension on 2 points. Curious how Mark did the dick. Billy almost made it on top of the dick. 8=====D
Shirley DG'd the stand so the sit gets the DG as well. Felt like hard V10 the way I did it but I used really dumb beta so it's soft 9.
This really made my shoulder sore. Cool movement, definitely contrived. And soft. Are you experienced has gone in 2 parts, no way will I ever link it up though...
1st go. So easy. Like maybe V8. Still taking the pointzzz.
Shucks. Nice climb, punted the fraish! So many different betas to be had.
Not a good style for me, but so much fun. Barely fraished, glad there's jugs at the top... of everything
Warmup after Creaking Heights. Knew I wasn't gonna make it a day without trying hard. Felt quite easy, perhaps 10... but when in Rocklands, take the points?
Beautiful rock, amazing sequence. Totally numb, cold in the shade today!
Pretty brutal. Definitely looks better than it climbs, but it looks like the coolest thing ever so it's still good. Managed the no-cut-feet ascent
Harder than Royksopp? Definitely not but took more tries. Like a lot of things here, could be easier.
Everything is rad here. 2nd go soft for sure.
Felt hard. So good, Dor got a quick ascent!
Brutal. Hardest flash to date, almost fell at least 3 times but somehow pulled it out. Another one with a sick sequence!
Actually way cooler than I thought it would be, taller and climbs better. Plus it's so damn gimmicky I mean come on. PSYCHED on this place.
Cool climb if a bit contrived. One really hard move... Soft?
Idk what 7b is still, so dg time. Super sick and kinda techy. Are there any bad problems here? Well I guess the sit to this...
All of these 10s could be easier out here, but we'll wait on house consensus to pass judgement. Super fun, although contrived. Triple dub frash day whooo!
Really hard with Will's sandbag beta.
Rad one. Might be a softy who knows. Givin away stars out here like it aint no thang
Really really hard.
Sick climb, classic undercling crux. Mark right after on the fraish train!
Shweet problem, more obvious than Berserker but less fun... right after Berserker
Fun lowball roof. Lots of power on big holds.
Kinda serious and hard! Guess I maybe just forgot how to mantle since getting here.
3rd go. Kind of annoying to place the kneebar somewhere besides where your hand is, but really fun movement once it works
Put my hand over the lip and didn't grab on the flash... Well it's rare to get a one two step dyno outside so still psyched! Brian and Brotha B followed, fun to watch the shorter guys fly.
5 goes, hardest 8a in Rocklands yet? Still soft. Way to be Julian!

Yesssss really wanted to do this one bad, definitely a trip goal. First hard one would be a dyno! Brotha B led the way this time and I followed, but had to rapid fire for an hour to make it happen. Felt unreal to stick the slot, so psyched on this probably easier than V12 gimmick! I leave you with wise words from Brotha B, "It's impossible to grade, but it's definitely not 13".
Another one I grabbed and then let go of on the flash go... shucks. Easier than hole in one for me. Good first week out here, softies aplenty as promised!

Harder than I thought it would be. Most of these dynos feel the same grade...
Julian and Ethan on the follow up!
Probably V10. Keep rocklands soft! Super fun! Triple double flash day softies literally at every single turn!
Sick body positioning on this one. Crimpz
Less than 10 tries. Fired it right after Dan, sharp and aggressive! Psyched to get a hard one done this early in the trip. Quintessential rounds out the quintuple double for the day!
2nd go softing like it ain't no thang. Kinda scary, numbed out on my first go.
Keep rocklands soft!
Moderates are so hard. Super sick!

Felt really really hard but took me less than 10 tries so it must be soft. Executed perfectly on my last go of the day and it came together! Climbing 13s in a session... this is what Rocklands is all about!
This and Pendragon have been the only things that have taken me more than a session so far... Fun dyno! Super annoying start.
Felt hard last session, must have been tired. 1st go today, felt really soft.
Super softy could be easier but first 12 fraisher helll yeaaa. Spock pinch is sick!
Should have known double heels would be the way for me, blew the fraish. Oh well, super sick boulder with amazing pinches!
So bad. And soft.
#keeprocklandssoft
Julian with the flash and Will with the FBA! Amazing, nearly perfect rock climb. So psyched.
Felt easier but I'll take 11. So psyched on this line, perfect movement up on it's own pedestal... Trip goal complete.
Dynoless. Definitely not 11. Taking high grades to #keeprocklandssoft
Favorite one in Rocklands so far! Smooth jugs up to a jug to jug dyno high off the deck. STELLAR
Felt pretty easy and it's not really my style. Honestly no idea on the grade. Super fun movement! Love the heel release jump off the perfect pinch.
Flash go was kind of a wash, but psyched to do this line fast! Best hard line so far... Nate sent right after.
Should have fraished... Brother B thinks EZ so soft 10 it is. Super fun!
Could be V7, #keeprocklandssoft
Hardest climb of the trip for me, but I suck at open hand climbing so def soft 11.  So cool!
Thought it was hard but I'm weak so there's that

Such a fun core tensiony boulder! Punted 3rd or 4th go at the end and got flash pumped, then pulled a send out of my ass to maintain the 8B in less than 10 tries streak! Surely this can't continue, but for now I feel like Midas, except instead of gold everything I touch turns to soft.
Felt hard but I wasn't warmed up and went for the pioneer flash. Cool moves!
So soft I couldn't flash. Weird knee tweaky heel toe cam, but a spectacular problem nonetheless! Views up here are gorgeous too...

Impossible to Soft, a climbing documentary, coming soon to theaters near you. 
Also what a dabfest.
Sick, pretty hard, and with a full value topout and beautiful views.
Felt like solid V12 to me, had a really hard time getting my ass/earth magnet off the ground. After the first move it isn't too bad though. Great movement, aesthetically not the greatest.

Gorgeous line requiring balance, power, technique, and a cool head. One of the best in Rocklands, it's gonna be tough figuring out which of these amazing lines is my favorite... Would be V6 in Yosemite.
Feeling sick, walking up the hill to the crag was really hard. This felt difficult as well... Safari will be a good chance to recover.
Super fun, maybe easier but so is everything so who cares #keeprocklandssoft

One of the worst climbs I have ever done, but as Brotha B would say, had to hit this one for the "Comedic Value". Mildly raged for a bit, as it felt impossible, but soon found a toe scum to make it easier. Impossible to soft volume 2.
ascents.zlaggableName: In the Middle of the Ass

ascents.comment: If you finish left like the book suggests without using the obvious jug right next to the start this thing is seriously fucked. Maybe I was tired at the end of my third day on, maybe it was hot as hell, or maybe y'all are higher than my left nut is over my right and this is sandbagged in both difficulty and quality.
Lowball, but as Mark would say, "It's a movement testpiece". Took a while to figure out the beta, and initially I was pretty pissed, but the sequence is quite nice.
Didn't feel too bad, did most of it static except the foot cut sequence. Really cool but a bit contrived, as many lines are out here with all this heavily featured rock.
Too pumped to flash. Sick one.
Felt really hard to me but I'm sure the kneebar if used properly makes it soft.
Felt hard for me but only because I don't like the holds much. Wasn't doing so hot until Bryce send... but obviously send trained on his heels.
Stupid and really hard for me. Worth it? Definitely a hatefuck send. Everyone at Royksopp saw me top this out after much effort... shame on me.
Easy with a kneebar. I'm an American bigot so 7B doesn't exist to me.
Cool feet first sequence to a squeezy sketch topout. Surprised I didn't hear more about this one, it's good!
Used OG beta felt 11 ish. Also my skin is wet so maybe it's easier... starting to get shut down out here, ready to work for it!
Watching Brotha B on this one was like watching a train wreck waiting to happen. But he somehow sent without further popping his P... This climb really sucks.
Took me a long time but it's a personal problem. Definitely physically V7 but I suck.
Easiest dyno in Rocklands, but kind of highball so plus 3 grades? SO FUN
Very nice one, climbed it quite shakily but it's a rest day so to be expected.
Very nice, too pumped after a long day of climbing first session on it, but that just opened up the M Flash. Ethan's first 8B soon!
Hate underclings. Still not V12. Yatta boyz sending back to back all day erry day
Definitely said I would never try this, but Yatta Boys were having such an epic day we had to get on it. Both sent easily, difficulty of the full line is dubious...
Definitely much harder after the break, is what I'm saying while I take 7C+ for this V8

2 sessions with OG ish shoulder beta. Not too hard, but definitely a bit techy at the top. Bryce came up HUGE with a send of this after being basically dead from too much climbing. BIG DAY for the Yatta Boyz.

3 sessions, kind of epic for me. Thought I would be much less psyched on this because it's lowball and long but it looks good in person and is soft so problems solved. I can't pinch and have poor power endurance so this must be quite soft. Bryce almost followed, and death screamed all the way onto the ground. Vice president is definitely the obvious better line. Start of an epic day!
M flash. AKA Tomorrow I, Will, Be Gone. Felt impossible first session but I knew it would be soft shortly thereafter. Sick!
Too many rest days so we went out in the rain, and somehow despite the boulder being soaked all the holds were dry. Sent in the dark in just my undies and a kneepad. Psyched on my first 8B+.
Lowball underclings? Sick. Psyched it was raining otherwise I wouldn't have slid off the V0 topout once before sending. Probably my favorite lowball undercling V11 cave in 8 day rain.
Felt hard until everything clicked 4th session and it felt leagues easier. Such a good problem that was definitely high on the list ever since I've gotten here, and I thought I might not pull off.
Very easy if you can reach the jug, looks fucked if you have to jump... Super sick problem!

Sent fast in a session, very uncertain of the grade... Hardest move for me was definitely getting to the peanut. Could be V12 for sure but I'm going to #keeprocklandssoft on this one. Amazing movement testpiece!
Really hard for me but so many dgs it must be soft...
Mileage day because I'm only 5 days on, gotta get a workout in.

Harder than the Vice but still soft. Really wanted to DG, thought it would be easy when I did the crux static in Iso, turns out it's harder from the start... glad Bryce viced today I never want to come back up here.
Quite fun all things considering. Well one thing considering in particular. Well I won't say what that is of course.
Almost flash trained my first 8B+ with Bryce, would have been sick. Did it a few goes later.
Sick climb, almost flash pumped on it.
Pretty unpleasant, don't get the hype. Guess it is a cool line, with a more obvious start than the stand. These safety ticks are getting heinous.
Call me Captain Choss because I spent the last 3 hours screaming, cussing, and battling my way through four mediocre to chossy boulders (plus a fail on Skobbejak). Yatta!
Besides the obvious jug rail following the climb the whole time, the kind of heinous holds, and the lowball nature of it, it's actually ok.
ascents.zlaggableName: In Search of the New Sound

ascents.comment: I think this is the problem I did... couldn't figure out how to pull into the undercling from a sit so I pulled the first move with basically one hand and it felt heinous.
Best one of the day, wish I had some more pads to try the cool stuff. Moves well, not a good warmup though.
3rd ish go, great rock, super softy! Not a fan of the underclings though...
Nice mega softy. Salim Andeep thinks V6 but I can give 7.
first go, but sixth go. weird drop knee ftw
Pretty hard, super shouldery. It was 80 degrees out and in the sun so maybe not hard? moves are kind of cool.
For those of us who are way too weak to do both dynos on Encore, I pioneered a lame and weak way to top out after the first dyno. Yayyyy me!
Super long, almost fell off the end... faaaa. Worst I've flashed a climb and still sent.
Fun jump, kind of hard heel up ass move at the top.
Fun kneebar climbing, much like Gliding. Mateys kinda sucks though, only downside...
Really fun line on an amazing boulder out here at Taj Mahal. Glad we made the trip! Bryce had to jump for both the crux moves which I did static... looked really hard and was quite impressive.
Sick press out onto the radical egg files feature from the sit start. Futuristic!

So fucked, def the hardest problem I've done this trip but also a one mover so who knows... if it truly is a V12 one mover that would be the hardest move I have ever done, and that feels about right. I can see how it would be really easy if you're strong, but I'm not. Guess it's soft. Thanks for the beer Will! 75th double d of the trip!!!
Wow so soft but also pretty good! Not a fan of these undercling moves...
Found a crimp out right makes this a lot easier! But seriously, kind of cool for a contrivance.
Slogged through the ankle deep marsh to get to this one... wasn't quite worth it but the others rounded out the experience. Pretty cool moves, super lowball and moist.

This is the kind of sequence and movement setters have wet dreams about creating. Intricate foot and hand sequence up a sick fin. Tried it on the way in, couldn't pull on due to glassy skin and warm weather, then came back after a full day and sieged for a few hours, steadily losing stamina but cleaning up my sequence just enough to validate continuing the session. Full value for me in these conditions, but if it's cold and I'm not weak could be super soft...
Beautiful line out a steep roof that climbs well and isn't dabby. Glad the marsh was worth braving!

Mantle straight out the obvious roof in front of the Mobil Mart. Thought it was harder until Konkey Dong made it look so so soft. Feet first variation is quality as well. A must do for everyone who can climb this grade.
A bit late to the party with this one, but really psyched to climb it after repeatedly greasing off the top last time. Great line, great weekend with lil D in the meadows.
Easier than T-bird for sure, so soft 11 seems fair. Back to back sends of T-bird then this one, psyched!
Almost M-flashed from the low today. Must have been really weak last year this felt impossible. Nice to be back, I love it here!
1st go soft. Already did ftg and the other link tho so no flash.
1st go soft. Kinda hard.
Felt hard a last year but then this C Hoss kid did it so I figured it must be easy. Also I heard he didn't actually do it 2nd go.
Weird one. Kneebars are hard to grade...
Thought this was pretty fun. Cool features
Hard and shitty. Woohoo!

Never thought this would go, but it wasn't so bad, sent 2nd try from the start. Spent almost 3 minutes navigating the 720 degrees of kneebar rotations, but pulled it out in the end. Very entertaining and difficult for me, but soft because the hardest move is probably V7.
Felt hard to me. Sick line! I'm a sucker for anything that ends with a jump.

Super fun one way at the top of the talus field. Interesting face crimp compression into full blastoff for the lip over a weird landing... sweet. Shoutout to Dor Damien BK and Jess for hiking up and giving support! Super softy at 12 or maybe 11...
Fun double clutch dyno to some slopers. Couldn't get all the way back to the jug...

Just jammed my thumb, and I have bad wrists so the over your head cocked sidepull hold with a key thumbcatch really felt amazing for me. Somehow managed to climb it... and it is cool. Psyched my 200th V10 was originally given V9.
Rad hard problem on a cool feature, complete with a sketchy slap topout. Super fun
I would call this soft but it took me 2 hours and I almost didn't do it. Ran out of excuses on this one, I think I'm just really weak. Barely pulled it out, fingers are screaming.
Really fun sequence. Glad I still have my foot. Worst flash ever, even with beta being sprayed at me.
Can a triple double be any more desperate than this? Was within a couple goes of giving up on every single climb I did today. Fighting hard.
Few tries. Not so bad, super fun. This boulder is pretty sick...
Taking the pity points for how much pain I'm in. Probably V9, however as you will note there does appear to be a troll in our midst... Retro DG because I can't take 10 pts. Still not V7
Very nice, very easy. What a good looking face.
Glad I could be here for Bryce's Northeast trip! He is really killing it.
Incredibly hard for me, my arms don't function when they are that close together. Didn't start at the super low low sit but Bryce did... still taking it, I almost fell off of every single move.
I don't even know what to say this thing is so weird. Damn you double down...
Felt about as difficult as Roses, but some last minute beta tweaks made it feel easier... hmm. Very nice problem! Still fighting hard for every send I can get my arse up.
Sick. Repeated in the sneaks for Ss and Gs
Absolutely heinous for me, but then Will and Bryce sent so I had to try hard and bear down. Nice looking face, kinda unpleasant climbing.
Felt like V12, but I know it's not. Hard when it's warm... plus my skin was rolling ;)
This is a pretty amazing line. Had to alter the trip plan a bit to improve my chances of sending and it paid off. Perfect last move! So fun.  The gloves are now OFF!
Sick complete with a futuristic mantel.
My fingers hurt so bad but this thing is so cool!
Uhhh... Super direct is next? The gloves really came way off today. Like way too far off.
So many beta options, eventually ended up with a hybrid of Bryce's and Jake's. Glad to have all this beta!

Nice low start to Touching. Had to do it for the name. Day is shaping up to be nice after everything was soaking wet at 3AM last night and it was pouring rain still and Bryce and I were depressed but now it's beautiful and look where we are
A few tries. Not bad with heel over head beta. Jake's OG beta looks hard. Sit goes... I guess. Finally matched Max's day! I just wanna be like him. 150th double d this year... let's keep it rolling!
Heinous. Terrible. so unpleasant, but I just want to have a day like Max so here I am.
Easy if you're tall and can lock off. Amazing boulder with amazing movement. So good!
Thought it would be hard for me but not so bad. Topout is kinda sketch! Oh Joe....

So named after much deliberation for it's short stature and condensed difficulty, as well as to jab at the kid who punted the FA 4 times on the last move. In classic fluke fashion... SNAKE! Thanks for the tour Jake! Low start on 2 underclings to the double undercling up road from the main parking lot. 2 methods, Bryce's felt impossible. Started getting desperate on this one and almost lost the big day...
Kinda hard for me especially with chuffer beta. Reunion with Liam!
M flash P flash whatever you wanna call it tried it a long time ago then did it first try today. Pretty nice!
Bad warmup. EZ with heel jumpless method.

Maybe the hardest soft 10 I've ever done. 1.5 hours soft. Almost blew my whole day here, on the 2nd problem of the day... Nice vision B Nugs a real gem. If the stand is V8 it's probably actually only V9...
2 sessions over 4 years. Finally felt soft. Actually still hard for me but it's not my style. What a line!
A few tries. Kinda heinous left hand but pretty fun for a one mover!
Took a few goes. Realized walking up here I blew my flash 4 years ago when I was more of a chuffer than I currently am. Didn't M flash anyways so who cares.
Crimpy, crappy, and easy just how I like it. Yatta boyz train

Surprised myself and Mark with the day 1 fluke after a miserable day at Mortar. Nice moves, although there is somehow still a sharp hold. Def a body position boulder, once you're in the positions it's not so bad. Impossible trav gets the didn't go soft from Mark and I.
Felt hard and improbable but the first thing I thought when I stuck the first move was "soft" and so it is.
Super fun weird vertical toe hook-crappy sloper compression. Very physical and bizarre.
Brutal one mover. Took a few tries. pretty miserable. But props to Craig these lowballs are a proper challenge!
Kinda scary, took a few tries to gather the courage to go for it with only Chen Chen spotting. Not bad if you're tall though when you commit. Probably V6-11 depending on height. Fun problem!
Feels like it falls on the upper end of the spectrum grade wise. A nice problem with an exciting finish, the cocaine corner of Redrocks!?

Amazing line, Vice of Red Rocks for sure. Except lower angle. Gonna keep drawing comparisons here. Felt solid to me but it was hot today and I don't like close compression underclings. Had no friction at the top, had to resort to bs chalking maneuvers to send... Still managed it in a session though.
Nice line in baking sun. Moves well, and feels a bit insecure at times. Sweet.
Wanted to give V4 for Sophia but fell almost fell off... so hard
Silly and contrived. But in the shade so that's a plus.
Hard at first, then after a lot of repeats and sussing not so hard. Full value topout!
Amazing line. Very easy if you're tall. Sure looks hard for Chen though... good thing he can jump.
So hard for me. But Dylan did it so it's soft. Jumped to the crimp off the 2 finger pocket and campused, it was miserable.
Saw this nice little line and just had to climb it. Super fun!
M flash on this one. Hard for me still, topout is tough as well. Solid at the grade.
Hard cuz it's slopers, which means it's actually soft. Fun climbing on nice holds, kinda a battle.
Harder than Lion's share, but that could be easier than 8 even so 8? Seems to be easier for shorties, says Chen.
Sit to Need Water down and left on a huge undercling rail. Adam couldn't do it... Shame! Shame! Shame!
Adam and Max's little problem next to the big bloc in the wash. Fun two mover.
Max gave it V9 but I don't see a V9 climber ever having a shot at this one so I'm giving it 10. Up from the big bloc by the cool V3 in the hole. 2nd ascent it sounds like...
Felt tough but I know it's soft. Pretty cool moves, at times awkward. Nice flash Chen!
Hardest V3 ever. Until it wasn't.
Cool rail in a spectacular spot. Don't blow it...
Cool campus problem by Austin Geiman on a sweet pinch... has MZ written all over it. Slightly harder than the other campus I thought was 10 so I guess 11. 2nd?
Took the swing once and landed perfectly just at the edge of the pit with no pads in sight. After almost dying decided to change my beta to keep the foot on. Such a cool problem!
Few tries. Silly but fun. Chen almost epiced, but wrapped it up just in time. Fell off the top of Atlas a couple times... Nooooo

Was hoping I would M flash this after my miserable sessions a couple years ago, and this time with bullet skin pulled it off with no warmup. Hardest move is maybe V7. Used Pete Lowe OG beta. Happy to be done with this...
Super dumpy but cool movement on weird unpleasant holds. Figured out the beta in a few tries with Mike then sent. Will never do Ackrite nor Redirect.
Or is it? 3 star rock quality and movement with 0 star height. Shout out to Max for cleaning and spotting this one. On the boulder sitting atop Skunk Sandwich and Leprechaun.
Spectacular line with sweet holds, great movement, and a tricky topout. $$$. No shame for Adam on this one!
A few tries. Prime conditions today, and Max took it down too! Solid. I think this one deserves three out of 4 stars.

Sick compression on improbably bad holds. No move is too hard but linking it all up is exhausting; never been more tired topping out a boulder. Hard for me because I'm lousy on slopers, but pulled it off somehow. Also no good when it's too cold and dry, had to moisten both hand and hold to send in the 3rd session. Psyched!

Best day of climbing for me ever. Almost was already with Abby and Phonebook before this, but now it's just surreal. Reverted to the heel hook method because it felt easy, even though I don't like it. Feels like solid 12 with the heel, at least 13 OG method. Abbatoir is harder for sure. Never thought I would see the day... YATTA!!!

Actually 10th session soft. Turns out there's a slightly different foot, m-flashed with it. Never thought I would do this problem. Liam and Chen both showed me up! 2 stars because I love and hate it. Two problems I thought I would never do in a day? What!!??

Wow. Was not expecting to do this anytime soon, but psyched I did! Couple sessions to get to the last move, couple more to stick the last move and then send. Pure, and just as challenging technically as it is physically. Topout was wet took me 15 minutes to get down. Carlo and Mark's back to back comments are gold.
Easy, dunno why I couldn't do it for all these years... get rained out of the milks and this is what it comes to
Took me forever. Tough and really bad.
Nemesis mega proj for me. Almost did Man-Dance too today after somehow unlocking the moves... Terrible. How has this gotten 3 stars.
From the stand. Had it in 2 majorly overlapping parts 4 years ago, but everyone does and can't do it. Until it's soft of course. Psyched to finally put it down...
Glad to see I'm stronger than I was 4 years ago! M flashed. Alex gave a million goes, but will send easily when fresh... Almost had a sick no fall day if I hadn't tried Haroun. Curse you Haroun!!!
Wanted to do this ever since I saw the video of Mark sahting his way up this testpiece. Sent first try 2nd session this year after punting the previous time. Psyched to finish this iconic prow!
Easier than the swarm. a couple tries, think I've got that move on lock now. MARK!!!!!!
Low sand makes this kind of sick. Dunno why this took me so long, Could be 10 but I'm taking high grades now so I can call them soft. Chillin with Dylan on X mas eve
Jugs on jugs to a tricky topout. First touch skin to rock... getting psyched on this place!
Cool holds, sequence, rock, everything... plus a sick improbable feeling move to the lip. The South!
Felt heinously hard first go, just hard second go. Soft.
It has got to break...
3rd go shame on me. Crimp felt solid, especially because the honker heel holds. Involved.
Pretty easy with the hand heel beta. Real good!
Super fun, but a bit overrated.
Span dependent. Such a cool feature.
Tried hard, almost fell off a couple times. Definitely got lucky on this one. Psyched!
Warming up way to fast and getting way too psyched!
Hard, reachy, and pretty unpleasant. Looks nice though!
Basically the easy part of mid size man. Prob soft for 9 but hey I'll take it. First go no flash climbed honeycomb before.
Really hard for me. Had to go feet first. My back hurts so bad from flying high omg
Lots of sussing, 1st go from the start. Mark flash? ;) had one shot, barely pulled it off. Way too much climbing.
Last climb of the year!  Super fun. Didn't make the 200 double ds goal this year, but did get the consolation prize of 100+ 8As so I'm psyched.
Hard for me. Last one to send like always :( shame. shame. SHAME! Forced it.
Last move is so sketchy how does your hand stay? Technical, and very very good.
Brutal. At least this one isn't reachy, right Bryce?
So hard felt like 7 or 8 for sure but I flashed so must be soft.
So good. One of the best of the grade.
Sketchy! Exactly what I expected from southern climbing.
Blew the flash being weak. Nice ticks for the V0 topout whoever was here last.
If you can do this you should. Had to be dropped a chalk bag to survive the top, locked off a crimp to my waist. Perfect.
1st go. Super fun!
So good. And so reachy. Sorry Dor...
Pretty rad! Dor was so close... but end of the day and we were all wrecked. Jimmy and Nalle are pretty cool I guess
1st go after stand. Really tired.
Kinda sharp, pretty cool. Big moves everywhere.
3 or 4 goes. 1st move is really easy but the rest of it is kinda hard if you're weak like me.
Nice to be tall. Really cool sequence, generally just an amazing rock climb.
Spiked my palm on the pointless ticked point. Jump hard... way to M flash the hardest V12 in the world Zach
Rad for a trav. Almost fell off the top, but whaled and it was OK
Did it the blind jump method and even climbed it once. So fun, more like this plz
Not so hard. These features are incredible!
Tough start move to easier terrain. Worst of the 3, still fun!
Reachy af. So wrecked, what an amazing day of fun!
Yatta! Bryce clinched the flash train for his first 8A flash, super proud! Felt terrible this morning but tried hard and climbed surprisingly well. Pure.
Not so hard, but quite sketch. My hardest slab flash!
Impressive and precarious. And soft. Perfect!
Cool movement up a steep face. Feels fair for 6.
Not crazy hard, and really fun. Not that sandy either. Perhaps it is cleaning up!!??
Almost didn't try this after God Mod because of how much pain we were in but glad we did. Really fun. Sam's epic continues...

Hardest I have tried on a boulder ever, hands down. Also the most fun I've had on a boulder. End of the day, totally maxed, fell off the top 3 times. It was do or die, and finally I did. So happy. I love this place. Must do if you climb this grade or preferably 8 grades harder. Took everything I had and then some. SO SOFT
Hard for me. Really cool mini scoops
Tough one for me. Death crimp sahting! Way to go Dor!
ascents.zlaggableName: A Face In The Crowd / Out Of Africa

ascents.comment: So cold can't feel fingers. Both Bryce and my foot slid off on the flash go, so second go soft train it is. Had to force it.
Tall man friendly. All about big last moves!
Sick big off balance stand up move. More tricky than powerful. So effing cold holy cow
Sick line with great movement. Minus a star for death topout or step off, minus a star for glued hold. Rad still!
Perfect slopey smeary squeezy questy slab experience. Hardest slab to date!

Back to back with Bryce... was incredibly psyched upon flashing this dream line, but so much more psyched when Bryce flash trained it! Unreal, a moment I will never forget. Gorgeous looking line that climbs perfectly. Holy shit excellent.
Fingernail crimping was the secret. Heinous, 2 days of efforts. Soft.
Cool movement, but kinda unpleasant. Let's get this day started!
First try. Also tried going to the even farther jug, and basically did it but almost took Sam's head off axe kicking the tree. Good times.
Awesome boulder. Sick pinch, involved topout, it has it all. Plus you can sit on the topout...
3 way flash train with Bryce and Mark. Could be easier. Moves really well!
Pretty cool for a lowball with a double undercling start. So not that cool.
Easy if you're my height. Fun jump. Muffed the flash, shame on me.
Sick feature. Sidepull it, kneebar on it, mantle on it... Def a bit sketchy up top.
Basically flashed, but dabbed on the swing kinda butthurt but whatever. Did it again dabless yay.
Little extra spice with the bigger dyno. Huge dyno variation would be really hard from the start.
Sweet. Nice sized boulder with good climbing.
Sam didn't flash
Topped out so I guess it doesn't count

This has to be the boulder that least suits my body. Undercling twisted 20 degrees beyond my already damaged wrist's range of motion leads to a full body rip in  a 3 foot tall roof. How did I not dab or break my wrist. Also fell off the end once wow. Only redeeming quality for me was fist bumping the tree I was hanging onto and dropping.
Hard for me. End move wasn't easy but stuck the first move finally once and forced it hard.

I was told this would be easy for me, but when we looked at it in the rain I said it would be hard and everybody laughed. Went back to try and after 2 hours of switching between 6 different betas everyone was still laughing. But I sent finally and it's soft so joke's on you!
Really nice one. Almost fell off the move to the lip.
Fun climbing to a kneebar rest, then epic questy long topout holy moly bad idea in the dark
Brutal first move for me with the jump, holding the rip is heinous. Wish I was strong enough to campus. Good thing the end is really easy... he said before dry firing off the jug.

5 sessions or more? W/e befuddled by this one forever, Drewbie's reachy beta made it possible. Still hard for me though. Dropping off of a contrived problem in the rain never felt so good, so desperate for rock climbing

After a miserable and wet season in CA the rain tried to stymie my attempts to climb a boulder all the way out here in Utah, but I got one just before the rain. I'm out of shape, and only took a few tries, must be soft.  I'M BACK BITCHES.
1st go. I'm a punt gotta get back in shape. Proximity is nice out here
1st go. Always thought that this would be my first V12, so it makes sense that it's actually easier. Shoulda tried to flash, messed around on the moves before trying to warm up.
Sick problem with an improbable sequence. Harder than Bambi for me.
Not a good style for your boy but pulled it out desperately a long ways into the session. Sick line! I will get in shape yet!
Pretty sick moves into Mavericks.
3rd go surprisingly long and airy for how little it is.
2nd go from the sit start. That lowball down the hill is pretty hard.
Now that is a damn good boulder. Awesome tour and session with Jeremy and Eric.
Few goes. These long boulders are really tiring... gonna be in good shape soon!
Felt tough to me, used the shorty method to make it high percentage. Looks like we were the first ones there this season...
Nice foot options so all heights can do it. I hate underclings.
First go. Took the swing and lived!
A few tries. First move is really hard for me. Got so damn lost getting here, had to do it fast before the sun set. Def harder than lost, have to retro UG
Wasn't sure which one was easier. I guess this one was. Didn't know what the line was so bailed out the easy slab way. Guess I'll have to do the other top out some other time...
Sussed it out with tired fingers and body, and then forced it hard. Need a rest day! Like this area.
From the jug. Nice climb in and of itself, legit start has some sick moves and is a lot of climbing!
Very straightforward and soft.
Weird
Sick, tall, and sharp
Harder than it looks. Got good temps and I'm sure it helped a lot. Pure fosho. Bday send, and a bday punt!
An it cryptic, but moves really well for a little boulder! Marcus is slaying!
Go static or go home. Flash for Marcus!? Best off the couch bouldering day I've seen.
Hard for me, also the start hold was wet so climbed it damp... right after the direct.
Couldn't do the normal one so this seemed easier. A few goes. Awesome movement.
No such thing as 7B in America so soft 8 it is. Nice quick send Marcus! A bit lowball but very nice
From the Moon Dance start slot. Super fun, actually not that far... you will lose palm skin!
Absolutely fucked. Weird body positions, maybe I'm missing something but that last move felt really hard...

Spotted by Jeremy, disparaged by Gregory, cleaned and attempted anyways due to Jeremy's obstinance... or was it Gregory's plan all along? One move wonder crimps to sloper jug on the boulder near the river.
This line is sick. Sit sucks.
Awkward moves into the stand.

Got to the pocket move twice first day attempting, then went on to continue to fall there for 4 days including once after sticking the pocket and once off the slab. Then I broke the huge foot in the middle section, but other beta works fine. Once I got my new intro sequence dialed felt like V10/11 into the stand which I guess is 11/12. Hardest I've worked for a boulder in a while, can't really grade something like this.
OMG so aggressive ouchie
Kinda contrived and a bit chossy but the real detractor is all this grade drama.
10/11 not really sure. Taking the grade because the start jug was soaking and water dripped in my face mid ascent. First go after doing the stand, felt easier musta climbed it better.
Tricky move into the slot. Nice problem! Lotta ways to do this it seems.
Working out this part in case I ever manage to do the first couple moves.
You get lucky or you don't on this one. Got a solid spraydown from the crew and got lucky!
Did not execute very well but forced it. This is turning into quite a day, trip dub fraish omg
Really weird problem. Felt impossible until I got the positioning just right, and moved the left foot wider. Then it went immediately. Thanks Dustin for leading the charge!

Just another stupid and hard link up done by a bored person who lives too close to the crag. Maybe someone else has done this and not claimed it because its stupid. Maybe not. A few hard moves from Bambi links into the stand of Fantasia. For sure harder than Fantasia, intro boulder is a grade or two harder. Someone else come do this stupid contrivance and tell me how hard it is, am I selling it yet? One more way harder line in the cave left... I guess I'm still on the team!
A few goes, kinda heinous. Hit the big hold a little low due to an accidental toe hook, and consequently had to do a one hand bump up while barn dooring. Lucky!

My name is Faniel Dong and Barrel Rider V13 is the best hard boulder I've done so far in Colorado. Sent at the end of 2 very long sessions, fell off the end more times than I'd care to admit. So soft.
Had to try 150% incredibly difficult for me. Was 75 degrees tho and has been done in tennies so must be soft
No way in hell is this V5. But also it's a classic so it's definitely V5.
Could be easier, felt like there was no way I could fall. Also doing this 10 times in a row would still be easier than Things Done Changed.
I did what had to be done to get to the top. Should have warmed up, felt like shit and climbed about the same. Almost came down at least 10 times. Let's goooooo
Very soft, but I'll take it. Surprisingly easy for me to use the undercling pinch, I must be evolving. Bryce punted the stand a few times but did both, which was sick.

Cool for a trav. Moves well, kinda dabby tho. Any of those moves would be really sick on a face climb but when you do 7 of them in a row and are still touching the ground they somehow lose their novelty.
A few goes. Sick holds, movement, rock quality... haven't climbed anything like it!
Felt hard to me, but I think I used some bad beta... 1st go already did mind matters.
Miserable and very hard for me. Bryce saved me with hybrid heel beta. 3rd session, some piles are harder to climb than others...

Surprisingly the ass dragging sit doesn't make the stand any better. But it did make me tired enough to almost slice my entire pinky open on the jug. Good thing I bailed, sent a short while later. Never. Ever. Again.
What a shitty boulder! Somehow didn't impale my hand. Full foot cut to give the extra split second of time to place my hand safely.
YES! Tried a few years ago and it felt really hard, sent in a couple goes first day of the season this time. What a beautiful line with sick movement!
I've done harder V7 lip traverses and never done an easier V10 (or V9) lip traverse but I'll take the quad dub.
Glad I hiked up here just for this. 7 grades harder than Gobot.
D O P line with a super satisfying stick at the end. 2 sessions, go in the morning so you don't get sun in your face.
Probably never going to climb the link into this. But this one is ok.
Somehow didn't dab, what a proud line!
Snow was really high, probably touched a backpack strap. Moves well for a trav, low end.
So frustrating, but also pretty cool. 2 flukes in a day! Heel placed terribly, panicked and my foot somehow fell into a bomber toehook position. Much wow.
I knew I was going to send when I finally stuck the crux move in isolation once and had the climb in 5 non overlapping parts. First fluke in a while!
Can't believe how long we spent looking for this 3 years ago. Heinous for me. Soft.
Eric thought I might flash it and it happened. Fancy that! Super fun. Low end at my height.
Tall and scary at the top. Went up to look at it and it looked undoable, but really just should have more than 3 pads. Also had a rattlesnake in the landing zone. Nice work Jon!
1st go. Good moves. Hard.
Hard for me. But I did do the crimp method in 80 degrees...
Fun squeeze problem with weird moves and a hold I have never experienced before. Punted once but redeemed shortly thereafter. The slab was quite chossy and scary...
Wow now this is a really nice boulder! Sight for sore eyes after an hour in the cave under the lightning storm, glad Will made us stay to dry it off!
Felt pretty hard but was also not the best friction on these slopers. Cool compression!

First session I was ready to bunker down for a 10+ session epic, felt impossible. Second session felt the same until a few beta tweaks and some inexplicable heel stickiness just made it happen out of thin air. I am very fucking surprised.
Few goes, used shoulder match beta to make it fit me better. Dabby AF but it's an OK line.
Few goes. Hilarious, stupid, fun, and annoying all at the same time.
Super cool feature climbing with weird moves and a full value topout. Sick! One sesh to suss, and a night sesh with will and Zach to take it down.
Had to use a knee pad too tired omg. Lots of beta and stuff.
Much sicker but contrived climbing at the top. Eric and Jeremy built the landing up to make it a bit safer. This is what its all about.
Got tired, pulled it off at limit. Easy climbs made hard woohoo. Jeremy owes me Baba's
Too hot to be grading things
This isn't what I wanted. But it's what I get. Taking the soft high grade on this one. You either die a hero or live long enough to see yourself become the villain.
Sick climb!
Definitely nice being tall for this one. Fun afternoon sesh, glad we made it happen! Amanda will send soon...
Glad I could do the better line. Climbed poorly and had to try harder to make up for it. Great war for civilized asians!
Super cool sequence and fun climbing. Blew the fraish, but still got to follow Jeremy up for a send train!
Fun one that's surprisingly good and not dabby. Nice work Juliet!
Surprise send. Pretty hot had to try hard and ended up a bit desperate. I'm sure it's easier when it's cold...

Good moves on a small problem. M flash after a rough hot and tired first session. Got fluke cold conditions for two hours and got to this on the tail end of that and it felt crazy easy. Then it got hot again for nbs. Chen and Withey injured... just me and Kim on the send squad, although Chris did gimp flash up autobot and tommys
Actually pretty fun, double clutched at the lip. Kinda hard...
What a tiny little pile. Kind of fun tho. Felt crazy hard for two sessions then Chris came out to watch and damn it was easy.
Nice one Nick! Shoulder was not pleased with the abuse on the high percentage beta but it can deal with it.
I must have been very fat last time because this time it felt quite reasonable. Just gotta get the bike to slide in right on the first move, no double clutchery required.
Well, 3 easy campus moves added on... but considering all of the moves are really easy who can say it doesn't add difficulty? ah well 10 it is.
Not bad. Bicycle shoulder moves are nice.
I hate this side of the boulder but I'll never be done with it. Nice having the bro out for a weekend!

Crux is pulling the last sort of hard move after holding a 90 degree bent arm hang on crimps for a minute to keep your ass from touching the ground. Icing on the cake is the hole in my finger, but at least I didn't circumcise it, and I am actually happy because this one was hard for me and took a few days and now I never need to climb on it again. Plus it's classic so you gotta...

3 sessions, sent just before the rain with the parents supporting (no idea why they were psyched to come down to lincoln...). Cool moves, very reachy, super resistant. Always wanted to climb V15 maybe some day, feels like 12/13 into 10/11, but I do think I finally deserve soft 14. Couple minor dabs but nothing big enough to bother me (sorry Liam), psyched to be pushing through into some harder stuff! LETS GOOOOO!!!

Heel popped immediately on the flash go... whatever I'm not butthurt or anything. Cool feature. Rowland is right, Whispers is for kids. Kids who like climbing better problems than this one. But this is still cool! Made Conor worry about me on the top cuz I was so pumped.

Was told it was Topaz and I was like that shit's easy. Realized it wasn't and then it was kinda hard. Was starting lying down on the rail, that was lame, finally got it to come together from the crimp start just to realize my beta was so wack. Went to the crimp, crossed again to the shit block slot, then tensioned into the jug. Felt like 12 but that was bad beta so soft 11.
Felt hard, but then we started camming and it was soft. Classic dab crux. Finally got a mileage day in.
Gian is close to sending! Cool movement on heinously uncomfortable holds
5ish tries. Cool sequence, went for straightforward beta at the top. "Hard topouts" are proving to be pretty hilarious in CO. Could be 11...
Dabby and annoying. Otherwise kind of cool. Full line looks real. Real wide. And soft. But also not my style so hard.
3rd go. Reachy, but a rad one mover nonetheless
Purdy beta on this one. Super fun, and great rock!
Sick sick line, complete with a head height jug start, great movement, and an airy topout. That is one big dong.
Took a long session to figure it out, but it was like 70 degrees out. Dey axed me if I wants to come back when it's colder, and I says no. Man's not hot.
Can't wait for that Szechuan sauce
I don't always fall on 6s, but when I do they're soft. Shirley is surely climbing one grade harder every day!
Cool balancy movement. Almost done wth the boulder.
Lowest holds. First go. Weird circle. So tired. Nothing on this boulder matters anymore because its donzo.
From the lowest holds, seems more traversy than it used to be. Still fun!
Climb love off routing the big pinch following the way the original line used to go. Pretty stupid!
Pretty hard. But went first go with the right beta so must be soft.
Simple but with such subtleties. Was not expecting to send this so fast, felt impossible... until it went.
The Son of Claudius Rufus of Moraine!? Fun and not very difficult. 3 way flash train with the boys.
Somehow doesn't have a name despite it's sickness... felt like 8 or so without a kneepad, 7 with one... so prob low end for 5. Love this kind of challenge on a mod!
Starting from a natural start this is a lot lot easier than the other Atari... 3 ish for me.
Not a huge fan of traversing but it's ok.
No foot bullshit slammed into the undercling from the start holds. detracts from the real problem.
Heel toe cam is sick. Nice problem! Dor sent real fast.
That's a damn good boulder. Spent way too much time trying and failing on this when tired, felt pretty easy fresh. Topout was a wee bit scary going straight up...
Cool movement, a little dabby as always. Solid after work sesh with Eric and Tim, got it in a few tries.
The one move dyno just left of McMurphy. Start split handed and launch to the top. Good eye Alex! Feels hard and scary until you do it. 8A+ in Africa.
Few tries. Don't think any V10 climbers will be doing this any time soon. The direct dyno is sick! Good find Alex.
Beautiful impressive wall with good movement. Quite the stunner! Tag teamed with Jeremy.
Cool moves around a sort of heinous crux hold. Luckily, you use it for 2 moves then recycle it for a few more so thats good.
Start doesn't add much but I'll take it. Had some trouble executing but sent in a few goes.
6 sessions. I don't always upgrade, but when I do I earn it. Heinous for me, probably the hardest boulder I have sent to date.
Thought I was fat 5 months ago when I last tried this, turns out it is actually hard for me. Close compression underclings... low end for sure even for me though.
Almost didn't do it, desperate mulligan on last go of the day attempt to finish. Harder than dark waters.
Managed it without the kneepad. Fun little problem, a bit sharp for sure. Send train for Will and Juli!
What a line! Looked at it all summer over the water landing, finally dry enough to bag it. Good rest day in Eldo with the boiz
So hard for me. Today especially... end of DW is piss not sure if it even adds difficulty. But the beginning is so heinous.
Pretty lowball, pretty stupid, and pretty hard. I came in like a wrecking ball...
Nice one. The ladies crushed their projects today!
Good looking and fun line! Kinda good rock.
Need to learn how to turn my toes in. Personally difficult, but obviously not that difficult because I did it pretty quick. Glad I didn't have to campus the crux move.
ascents.zlaggableName: Ain't no heaven for a thug

ascents.comment: What a ridiculous move. Hard to grade for sure...
First go. Ludacris into the 8. Link ups for fitness at the end of the day, classic
Lot easier than Dark Waters, I'm with Purdy. Just gotta keep climbing contrivances and sit starts in this cave until I feel some sense of fulfillment.
Brutal. Welcome back to the valley bitch! Struggled all the way up one pad for the dirty topout pumped out of my mind was a little spicy.
M Flash after bailing off the slab years ago. Felt pretty shook after climbing only ass draggers in CO for a year... this is the good stuff!
Really good little 2 mover on bullet. Perfect post vacay boulder, power but not endurance. 3 goes.
3rd go. Everything is soft. Rough warm up for sure.
Super cool moves on smooth feet and at times sharp holds. 4 goes, I guess super low end or just 11 but I'm grading soft now so whatever. Proj is... doable?

Cool movement and bullet rock on suspiciously sculpted holds. Prob Yosemite V6 but we are in the land of the soft so here it is. Climbed into the stand once from the sit, then did the stand first try.
Cool little one! In this style... probably 2 or 3. To quote Dor on her dab ascent prior to her clean ascent, "Fucking shit!"
Barely could do the first move, but I could and its underclings so prob soft for the grade. Sent first time I pulled off the ground enough to move.
Small feet on polished granite with cool moves. Nice problems in the river here!
Possible FA to the right of Nobody. Squat start on low left sidepull higher right sidepull. Desperate cross saht to the lip, and some trickery leads to a desperate mantle onto the sandy beach slab.
Rock here is pretty cool! Hard ending section.
Jeremy sandbagged my flash to keep me from getting Baba's! Lotsa beta required here. Super fun.
Pretty hard for me. Harder than channel incision... big bump beta at the end!
Not my trip for fraishing. Second go soft city!
Great problem on southernesque sandstone. Amanda and Lavrisha will send soon!
Super good! Such cool rock, plus a little saht at the end.
Weird and awesome.
Mantle crux! Or really it's just weird up there. Sick line tho.

7 or 8 sessions, and a lot more effort than I was expecting for the training project. Felt easy today, sent first go of the session. Still way harder than wheel. Happy to be done with the cave, although there's always another stupid contrivance to do in there...
Right after Dark Waters Low. Felt to be in good shape today. Bonus fitness for the session woohoo

2nd day takedown, way too tired last time to have a shot. Striking line, good rock, cool movement even though it hurts my wrist. Had to take the pants off that's how you know it's getting serious. Best hard one I've climbed in a good while.
Tired at the end of the day, but glad we came over to see this wall. Cool problem, perfect height!
Project eliminating the large sloper from Carpet Bombers. End of trip fitness burn, almost pumped off of the top so tired...
Fun problem, doesn't look the most inspiring though. Not sure how I feel about cliff band bouldering...
Guess it's a bit harder than no tiempo, so if that's 10 than 11 seems right. Pretty fun.
Tough for me. Polished stone on a cold day is pretty slippery... weird mantle onto the slab. Had a good flash go then regressed for a few goes until I finally squeezed up the dang thing.
Kind of a dumper and super morpho. Hey guys what seems to be the problem it's easy look you just reach it like this

Crux is excavating your way to the start holds and then figuring out which of them to use. Probably started close to the right place, left hand crimp right hand on the arete same height as the crimp. Not terribly hard once you pull on, and not terribly enjoyable either.
Took a bunch of tries but once you know the beta it's actually pretty easy. Fun squeezing and toehooks to a grovel top.
Double toehooks out left is the way. Sick movement but wow it looks like shit. Dorian epiced and almost downclimbed from the VO topout, but eventually she sent! Proud.

Failed during a tired evening sesh. Came back, watched the boys flail "last go"s on the belly for 2 hours in slippery conditions then fired 2nd go. Also got reported for spray painting the boulder, but the cop knew what was up. Fun one Zach! Let the after work night seshes re-commence!

Almost took me two sessions, wish it would have. Satched it hero burn style end of the session in the dark with Tim. I'll still come back though, what a line. Not freestanding but still really sick. Stand start is pretty stiff for 6... After work seshes! Let's go! Daylight savings!
Few goes. Just gotta not be a weenie. Everybody sent!
Weird. I love flagstaff so much said nobody ever. Fun day with the crew tho!
Everything here sucks but at least it's easy.
Felt hard but if everyone says it's soft or V9 then I don't want to look weak so it's soft. Really hard tho.
Prob doesn't add a grade. I guess we started too low on the stand anyways. Similar difficulty, similarly shitty.
10 for me. Also nobody else sent so...
Hard for me for some reason. Not hard enough though pulled it off desperate boy style.
Easy for Yosemite VB, but I'll take 1 point for this. Super fun, techy and tall. Try the fingerlock only eliminate with no downpulls for a nice true crack climbing challenge.
From a squat. True sit is super hard, funny that nobody seems to realize that's how you're supposed to climb it...
Super fun. A bit morpho admittedly... at least 2 grades easier than Arrowhead ;)
Not too hard, decent enough though. Mileage day with the crew!
Slots V3 was a perfect project for Chris
Nice problem. I'll take the flash even though I already did the topout for Phish. Tricky.
Slow progress on this one. Gonna be a long time
Looked really easy, then felt really hard, then actually was pretty easy. Chris was here but he didn't do it just so everyone knows.

Wow happened a lot sooner than expected. Couple terrible sessions on it led to a fluke link to the last move 4 months ago. Turns out wasn't a fluke, dialed in the intro and fired in the snow. Doesn't everyone send this  one while it's snowing?
Weird one. Super bad warmup. Not sure where y'all get a knee bar but who kneeds it.
Fun one, bit of ass slam potential tho. Few tries.
Took a bit to figure out, thought it would be impossible from the low when I first climbed it but it gets easier as you learn it.

Could be 12, felt easy and did it in a session but I also fell off the end once and almost pumped out on the send. Trickier and longer than it is physical and difficult. Used a different sequence it sounds like, but everyone has probably used a different sequence there's so many holds. Chris was here today!
No idea how this thing goes and what's on and off, did a version that felt about as hard as death scream. Contrivances are sick, I'm never coming back to Joe's so sandy.
EZ with a kneebar. But people are prob taking 11 with a knee pad because they be weak af

Absolutely heinous feet first offwidth left of Baldwin Bash. Fun to get annihilated on something I don't know how to climb, barely pulled it out. Will have to return to eliminate the rest of the holds.
Didn't know this was actually a thing. Kind of hard definitely unpleasant. Good camaraderie tho!
Hard, and quality. If this is V8 Return of the Jedi is V3. Favorite b-day send this year.
Was told this was V10 but felt harder. Couple unpleasant moves into the stand.
Nice climbing to a fun mantle. Pretty darn good! First try but did Return first.
Return of the softness V8 my asshole. At least it's a contrived traverse. Pretty fun still, low variation is quite entertaining.
Actually quite a good problem with good movement.
Everyone gets to climb V10 if they can walk far enough.

Striking line with interesting movement, a full value topout, and a spectacular view. Add the sense of urgency provided by a rapidly melting landing and long approach, and you get a line that really feels worth it. Best hard line I have seen in CO. Felt easy for 12.

Cool beta intensive resistance problem. Tried during a tired after work sesh with Eric, then came back 15 hours later and dispatched first go. Does that count as one session? Tim says the topout crack is 5.9
Beginning was a bit unpleasant, topout was a bit heady, dirty, and questy especially with no pads. Good looking arete though.
A bit scary but not so hard. Nice with 5 feet of snow... Tim is getting honed
Hardest move I've done. Meaningful to send a condensed difficult boulder. Tried once last season, felt impossible, but did it in a session this year. Yahtzee!
Almost pumped out on a 4 move boulder. Consolation prize, topout was fun but a bit chossy. Good thing Josh had my spot.
A few goes shame on me. Fun climbing on jugs to a cool feet first exit.
Hard for me for some reason. Had to use the sidepull to get leverage cuz my legs are weak. Fuck you Tim day was going great until Chris' knee exploded.
Small and dumpy but when at Emerald... no other options for a new climb. Epiced on the end could have done it much better. Just had to impress everyone. Ethan flew off spectacularly.

Remembered this being hard from 4 years ago so I told the whole Madrock team it was then Jan made it look like a V4. Had no choice but to M flash to salvage a shard of dignity but it wasn't easy I just tried really hard.

After work sesh it goes! Tried so effing hard. 3 Sessions, ended up having to use the closest worst part of the crimp to get my wrist at the right angle. 6 foot span on me, with a few more inches prob V10 or 11, with less prob much harder. Double clutch method is ludicrous.
First big move is kinda tough. So many palm flappers... Well Tristan and I did not get 50 points today.
Super fun, pretty hard. Didn't jump but the cut was gnar. In the dark in the rain with Tim and Josh
Only took Bryce and I a collective 10 tries. I guess it could be hard, if it were a V3. Great first one of the trip!
Been trying this for years don't know what the big deal was... finally pulled it off with Bryce.
Bryce and I are LEGENDS.

Pure, aesthetic, and SICK! So psyched to climb this one. Thought about it a lot and just can't take it. Felt easier than just about everything else this trip including Busted V5. Bryce sent one go off of the train.
Couple cool moves in a small hole to a tight squeeze out of said small hole. Not very fun honestly but we did it...
Sort of close on flash. But then took a while to figure out the last move so maybe not... hot and smarmy but Bryce and I still pulled it off!
Super good. Can't believe I haven't done this before. Deputy fits me really well can't wait to cut both my arms off and send next year.

New age classic, Reckoning into Big Chicken. If it didn't off route the lip and the right arete would actually be really sick. Fun resistance climbing to a redpoint cruxy last pull on Big Chicken... If I stop now today is a rest day. Bryce got the Yatta train!
After all these years it just didn't feel very hard. Must have been really weak 6 years ago. The old "nemesis" goes down!

My biceps hurt so much from squeezing close compression all trip long. Bailed off the end first session cuz I was scared, glad the last rainy day turned out to be a great climbing day with sticky conditions so I could leave Squam with no regrets! Cool movement on weird holds, with a little spice.

Probably my new Go To Grand Wall warmup instead of the contrived summer vacation. Hitting some serious Rampage classics this trip including this and BustedV5. Yes you are seeing that right that is Zero Zero stars BTW.

After a heinous first session with a scary wet fire off the pinch somehow pulled it off. Glad I could just reach through the top instead of using the wormy undercling... Psyched to do this one! Finally getting my vert and slab feet back just in time to go back to CO and forget it all again. Surprised and happy to pull it off. Not sure what the weakest climber who could do this is but I'm pretty sure they climb less than V11... well whatever. Trip dub on the last day!

Jimmy's soft thang. Jk but I dont know the name so until then. Just right of Guillotine, rad opening moves including a gaston heel toe cam rose move lead to a big huck to the lip -2 feet off the ground classic lincoln. Tuck those knees to your chest for the swing! Great movement.
Wow somehow managed a trip dub at lincoln, thought I was tapped out. Although they're all soft and questionable. This problem kind of sucks.
Would be V7 but you actually have to try really hard to keep from dabbing. That was a pitiful warmup boys
A bit harder than the other entrance, especially when you climb it as badly as I did. Fully maxing out on every problem on this boulder.
Weirder and dabbier than it is difficult. One movers are hard to grade so I'll say it's soft.

Start for Residual Stress I think unclear from the video of the FA. Maybe start one hold up. Awkward and chossy, but at least the name is pertinent to the theme of the boulder. Ruined all my flashes doing Residual Stress first... sigh. Did 2 more sick variations up this wall for fitness lots of potential for eliminates
Blew my flash of contents under pressure and the easy one doing this first. At least this was the best one...
Super good. Bullet rock sweet holds and cool movement. Eric's hardest flash!
One of the last ascents of this one, at least in it's current state. Wow Tim was really messed up today.
Pretty good flash go, but couldn't pull it off. Sent a few goes later. Rad roof, cool movement, and seems accessible to all sizes.
Well I flashed something in this roof
Good movement, pretty easy at my height.
Good one! 18 feet tall with beautiful edge climbing. Second go shame on me. At least the boss flashed.
Weirder than it is hard, and certainly a very unattractive boulder. But hey I hiked up here and the movement is good.

This is the best looking line on the boulder! From way down in the hole straight out. Long and resistancy, but the only hard move is on Katana... Almost flashed to the jugs, had to return for a second session though and almost didn't send after a tragic punty foot pick at the very end on my first go. Second go of the day chicken winged it out but only barely...
Couple awkward moves into awesome tension climbing on rails and crimps, with a big lockoff to boot. Toughy for the grade.

Not quite as sick as the direct, and felt not quite as hard either... 3rd session counting direct sessions, but second go from the start. Too many easy moves to be 14 for me, prob more like 5.12d ;) For sure a step under the Wheel of Wolvo. I have endurance!
Fun climbing with less dab potensh than you'd think looking at it. Fell off the end on the flash go, sent quickly after. Inspiring watching Dean bag it last minute... Unsure of grade prob slasher.
Impossible 4 years ago with bad beta, pretty easy this time around. Rad climb with a rowdy jump, should have used the downwards bump beta on the send to make it sexy.

Life lister down! That movement and rock quality tho... Tito classic and well worth the hype. Stuck the first move second go, then flailed for a bit, but Liam hiking it inspired me to pull it off a few tries later. Almost fell on an unnecessary move I added would have been shameful. Fortunately didn't. YES!
Sick one! Couple hard tension moves at the end. Way to go Dor!
Sick one! Couple hard tension moves at the end.
First move to the sidepull is kind of hard. Pretty fun!
First move to the sidepull is kind of hard. Pretty fun!
First move to the sidepull is kind of hard. Pretty fun!
First move to the sidepull is kind of hard. Pretty fun!
Weirder than it is hard. Used the fabled down bump on this one to make the box fit me. Paul Justin and Emily were just making it look so fun we had to try.
Weird and kinda hard. Rough start to the day for Tristan and I. At least I did it. Gonna be desperado from the low.
Kinda scary at the top with no snow. Not even close to as hard as Tommy's.
Came for the camaraderie, stayed for the morpho contrivances. Pretty hard, but did it in a session plus one for Mind, so can't be too tough.
First go, but already flashed the stand. Takes 2 stars away from a climb that can't afford to give away that many stars. Go do everything else then come here.
Fun climb, weird and shouldery the way I did it. Dihedrals are pretty fun. Right next to Frontrange on Fire
The real one! Cool climb, one of the best of the grade at Lincoln, not that there's stiff competition.

Flailed for a while, on the first move, had about 20 goes of getting a tiny bit closer, then finally Tristan sent and I followed him up for the send train. Mike said I could lock it off if I was tall, but then my foot was in my face and he was wrong. Miserable boulder fun session.
Hard for me. Struggled it out, the one time pinching matters outside.
Slid off the top in the wet snow at the end of last season twice, thought about taking it but didn't. Came back and it was even easier than I remembered.
In a few goes. Got the cam to stay and didn't have to rip! Very odd problem, fun but low.
Walked past this a million times going by Bierstadt and never tried it, Justin sucked me into another classic. LMK if anyone figures out how this climbs as a 7. The down bump wins again!
Not harder than the original and certainly a lot worse. Do the OG first!
No hard moves and not really power endurance so I'm unsure of what makes this difficult. Probably nothing. Linked it up, directo on Aint no heaven is pretty hard.
Hard til it wasn't. Tristan gave me beta and it worked I'll be darned! Fell a couple times at the lip being sloppy but when it went it went silky smooth.
Few goes. Probably not a one move 10. Pretty spectacular location.
When did the world cup move outdoors. Crazy sequence, unbelievable that it's the best way to do it. Some day Chris will climb V10. Pulled it out of my butt day 2.
Really bad problem that I should have flashed but pump/numbed off the top of and almost died. Real men die on traverses. Thanks for grabbing me Purdy!

Cool resistance climb. No hard moves, actually not too hard to put together either... came to it fresh 3rd sesh and bagged it first go from the start. Just had to stop being stupid and forgetting where to put my foot for the heel hook at the crux. Guess I'll take the points but it's questionable, slasher for sure.
Can't tell if it's actually difficult or if we were just tired. Weird moves, not so good.
Pretty fun, weird sequence. Best contrived traverse at flagstaff on the cloudshadow boulder?
Sliced open my middle finger today, but still managed to three finger this thing. Good old traverses on cloud shadow with the sportiva boyz
Nice new one from D woods. Awesome feature with cool movement, unfortunately a bit sandy at the bottom. Pretty cold out today... Few suss goes then a few send goes.
Too cold to climb this many moves. Would almost (but still not) be cool if there weren't a million better easier exits you could take.
Had to try really hard. Kind of cool, too many hold options its overwhelming. Barely stuck the jump, desperate. Missed the send train with Bryce by 1...
