Changed my beta 4 times to try to avoid the dab but not make it impossible, finally figured it out and it came together. Incredible climb minus the start. Bryce almost had it 3 days on... he'll be back
Dang that’s easy with a kneebar
Step below every other V10 here, dropped off can I have it cuz the top was looking friable and wet.
Pretty cool problem. Loose Cannon ftw!
Send train with Tristan. Could just keep the kneebar. I think my guide is somewhere around here.
Really cool, too bad everyone dabbed.
Flash train with Tristan to make Marcus take us to the feather! Unfortunately he didn't believe us...
So good. Not a lot of rock this solid around Hueco. 3rd go, what a line! Send train city with T Chen

Incredible line, pretty intimidating with 3 pads. Tristan and I pulled off the buzzer beater send train with Marcus telling us we had to leave as I was sending. Last problem of the year, and top contender for best. Haven't been scared like that in a little bit! Tristan got drunk too and said a lot of nice things to me including that he was glad I was there ;)

End of the day desperation send. Two fingers on the good crimp, triple pull up to the the back two on the numb desperate top out. I won’t do slashface this trip but at least I did the better line he said
So good! Aesthetic tall line, rare for hueco. Bummed I missed this last trip.
Wrong foot beta with good intentions from Austin but I’ll take second go soft soft soooooft
Few goes. Knee bars are tricky. Really cool sequence!
The only remarkable things about this boulder are how easy and bad it is
Kinda hard, but not even close to as bad as I remembered. Tristan and I did anal, then we did a climb too.

So ludicrously hard for me. No knee bars, no feet first, all suffering and struggling. When I say it's soft V11 I mean it's actually hard but I feel bad with how many people have downgraded it regardless of how they did it.
Wrecked on the last day but barely pullet it off. If I have a talent it is climbing V11 and under.
Lotta different ways to do this one, had to hybridize when the toe wasn't staying. Everything in this roof is really cool and immensely shitty at the same time.
Few goes. Was definitely raining, but the holds weren't too moist until the ledge at the top. That was soaked so I dropped off but I need the points so I'm taking it.
Couldn't use the scrunch beta.
So good. Aesthetic and rad, and just easy enough up high to not be horrifying. Nice accidental foot cut Tristan.
Fun pure line! Prob shoulda flashed... got a couple more boulders on Tristan now ;)
Thought I might not do it til I discovered the heel for the crux move. Very cool, certainly not my style. Had to earn it.
Rad compression line. Few goes. Thanks for the spraydown Josh and congrats on the send!
Seems like 1 move 10 to me. Not very good or very impressive but hey the rock is good and I hadn't done it. Gotta secure that weekend victory over Tristan.
Really good. Nice and airy at the top too! Go for the dyno variants trust me. Didn't know at the time we were gonna be stuck in roy with 3 flats... ignorance is bliss.
Super cool climb with delicate movements. Slightly marred by the side wall that is right there... rad to see Nina put down the directo!

Feels like V6 into V11, but then it's kinda hard so dunno 12 seems fair. Couldn't fit the kneebar after I chossed off a bunch of rock trying to find one that would fit, but it's not really necessary anyways. After work sesh with Andy, tired but it's soft so pulled it off.
It goes boys. Second double d in CO this year. Productivity is at an all time high!
First go after Amendment. Cool moves! Weird style. Reverse hard boiled haha
Sloppy warm up flash.
First go after the stand. Super good movement, not too crazy hard from the left sit.
Way to fire the rig Sather! Mantle left is very cool but there is a much more secure and easier sequence leading right. Best V5 in CO?
First go, but did the stand and the left before. Mantle gets harder every time, probably should have gone right at the lip
3rd go shame on me. Guess it was 75 degrees. Sather with the Germ Free takedown!
Harder than it looks. Also worse than it looks which is remarkable all things considering.
Took a while. Don't like finger pockets, even super natural ones. Really good movement though, Mark fired it real quick!
Warmed up on this one, if someone told me V7 I wouldn't bat an eye. Pretty fun regardless.

Took a few sessions of being very close to sending to figure out all the micro beta I needed. Never felt much pressure to send considering I'll come back every day its snowing, but still happy to finish it off. Wild moves I'll probably never do on another boulder. I'd feel bad about dropping off of this one if most every sport climb wasn't just a dropoff someone decided to put chains at.
Took a while to figure out, but between sussing and trying really hard eventually got it to go in a fairly controlled way. Mega classic
Lot of ways to do this one, none of them very pleasant.
Very cool line, bit of a razor on the left pinky though. Sent in a few goes, didn't know we were giving highball grades to 15 foot tall problems these days.
Super good. Dor will send next time!
Nothing but classics
One of the best lines I've seen in CO. Tall, good movement, cool holds, spicy topout.
First go, but flashed Gandalf first. Cool and scary, though the traverse climbing isn't all that great.

Thought I almost flashed, then realized I couldn't do the move, then went jug to jug skipping all the hard parts and it was really easy. Like really really easy. Trip dub day with Conor on classics only!
I thought this was hard but I aint a bitch so it's V9
Proud flash for Tim! Some frustrations with dabbing and heel cuts, but did it in a few goes and it wasn't too hard.
Felt kind of hard but it was 70 degrees out so everything felt kind of hard. Super low goes... not easily tho
If this is one of the best 7s in the Poud I'll pass on the grade. Doesn't look like much, does climb pretty well tho. Tim was psyched, and at least we weren't getting eaten by a million ticks.

Mega softy, could be a slasher. Almost bagged it in a sesh right after doing it via freedom, but fell off the last move 3 times. Came back for the quick takedown, but not before watching Conor take the worst fall possible. Jeebus.
Didn't know there was a jug that made this easier, kind of a bummer. Whatever I did felt 10 ish.
I'm going to savor doing these piles one at a time, very slowly. Dropped off the lip twice last time cuz I was pumped and didn't want to sacrifice my alpine season, priorities.
Cool down project goes down! 8C and 8B in a day, but most notably I flashed Bulgin out. Won't have another opportunity for the 15 factorial any time soon, too bad I squandered it.
Sans crash pad just like in the old days. Most meaningful ascent today no doubt.

Really cool to get on a hard climb that is also high quality. 4 sessions, first two were basically figuring out the second move aka my crux. Had a ton of support from the homies and tried hard, psyched to get it done before the heat comes. Out of my depth in this grade range so I’m going with consensus.
Went straight to the flat gaston then locked off to the last hold. Again, why do I ever try to use all the holds. Washed day in CC
Very very easy and contrived. Fun movement, but immense letdown at V10... Static flash train with Bryce
Few goes, was two moves in when I heard someone say "Come on Bryce" and I was like oh shit don't drop the ball now. Simul send, somehow Bryce managed crazy footstab cut beta on Free Basin. Legendary.
Nootz
4 Sessions, 8+ hours. Worth every penny. Held the ultimately extended king swing and just barely grazed a pad. I'm really leveling up these days.

Possible FA of incredible choss, certainly did not think I would be doing a problem I hadn't done before today, but imagine the joy and surprise in my eyes to spot a lower undercling below the existing low start of Toxic Shock. Griffin probably already did this, but if not what an incredible and historic first and then second ascent I have claimed.
ascents.zlaggableName: Toxic Shock Lower than the Low Start Start SDS

ascents.comment: Sweet line, rare to see a feature like this. Close compression was too tight, had to match the sloper to go the lip. Tristan with the mega punt, maybe he will send in session number 3.
Sure felt hard to me. Started from the lowest underclings, top felt very tensiony, super bump in the middle is cool. Rad problem.
Fun movement on this one, line right of Behind the 8 Ball. I guess I shouldn't expect that anything at lincoln hasn't been done before at this point...
Pretty darn cool, psyched to climb new stuff at lincoln. Top is a bit chossy, got up there on the flash and decided to preserve my life by dropping and sussing.

Kind of hard not to dab. Realized it wasn't that bad with a heel instead of a toe, then bagged it. Tristan could have flashed... but did it "solidly" after a little sussing on his next go from the start.
Hardest one we tried today. One grade easier than full chaos? ;)
Easier than skipper D? If this was 1000 feet off the ground I would solo it for sure. Having said that very cool climb, definitely worth going to.
Took a bit of effort, had to work out the right beta. Plus undercling pinches not my specialty... pinch training day for Tim!
Couple tries, prob 10/11. Really fun moves on cool holds!

Quite a good one from Griff and Chen right behind now Nudda. Could be easier, but harder from the start than you'd think... I think I doubled my productivity for the summer today with the triple/quad.
Very unpleasant holds but cool line otherwise.
Pretty darn cool, very slippery though. Time to get back in shape!
This was as far as I was willing to walk for an hour long night sesh.
Little suspect grade wise but fun problem with cool movement.
Felt really really easy. After the left I was like... I should probably do the uncontrived  better line. First go.
Fun contrivance, prob would have flashed with better betas...
Super softy, very fun though. First problem of the day!
Tough for me on manufactured holds, they're so slippery. Crux move was easy in iso, but those chipped holds stole my chalk on every send go...
Fun, too bad I can't do the second move to the low...
ascents.zlaggableName: The right hand of darkness standstart

ascents.comment: Nails first move, but otherwise quite cool.
Few goes, repairing my battered ego after muttertag. Friends arriving soon!
Kinda hard for me, had a mini epic but somehow prevailed in the end. Ouch my pecs.
Pretty rad! Steep with cool features.
Awesome kneebar sequence in the most perfect of mini dihedrals. Way to fight for it Dor!
Super fun cool feature. This is why I need to practice on giant block volumes in a roof.
Super fun squeezer!
Really fun problem with a cool kneebar intro.
From the full sit, felt quite hard. Few hard moves into an interesting mantle.
For the record I can't lock it off.
Quite good! Though a bit lowball. Very cool movement and holds, and dare I say it, not one is chipped?
Sick
That was way more desperate than it should have been. Really flailed up this one, even with sprays from Ishan and Conor.
Absolutely brutal. Dragged Caitlin and Conor over here and got savaged by this thing for a while. Tough mantle on slippery stone with a hard pull off the rock as the kicker. Supremely entertaining.
Could be 8a eff if I know. Had two heel slips at the start then cruised the rest of it. Perhaps I will throw myself at the link...
Some really embarrassing flash goes going down on this slipper chipped river rock. Fun climbing!
Dafuq that's hard. And awkward.
Pretty cool intricate problem with lousy feet.
Slipperiest piece of shit made rock climb around. Next plz
Kind of not very cool.
Not too hard, pretty awkward though. Great looking problem.
Cool little jump with a lot of things that are off.
If you're going to manufacture a boulder do everyone a favor and don't make it shitty
Broke the left hand hold at the crux on the flash go, but probably wasn't going to flash it anyways. Still goes, did it a few desperate goes later. Woohoo dropoffs
Super sick traverse. Contrived and everything but rad feature and incredible gimmicky lip traverse. Psyched.
Really good. Dor was close! Maybe next time... Nice delicate climbing
Really cool problem with just the right amount of involvement at the top.
Hard until I started using the correct beta. Fun, and a bit of an involved downclimb. That left hand niblet is painful!
Sat on one pad, crux was getting off the ground. Not very good but pretty hard so that has to count for something. Nice flash Conor!
So sick. Almost slid off but reeled it back in with some effort.
Really fun minus the awkward intro moves. Managed it almost static with a heel later as well...

Really hard to grade this one... Almost did it in a session but didn't switch to the compression method until halfway through... then fell off the end for 2 more sessions because conditions didn't feel good, then finally bagged it and it felt so easy. Idk. Very cool sloper pinch though.
Start waay down in the hole. Felt hard to me! Also what's up with microcosmos.
SO GOOD! Rad mantle to powerful (and admittedly reachy) physical crux on perfect polished rock. Nice work Caitlin!
Nice committing crimp line! Shirley u could fraish!
Good flash go, prob should have done it. Took a few tries instead. What a cool position!
Not too hard. Pretty cool movement, almost dropped the flash with a heel slip...
WTF hard. At least it's really good. Cleanup day continues!
Few tries. Cleanup day success, managed 3 double digits inside 30 min to wrap up the day.
Brutal. Got revenge on last day cleanup day! Right hand method. Some funny videos out there of people jumping off the ground...

Ups and downs with this one, really cool problem but the crux for me was sliding off the abnormally slick tampered right hand hold. Came back again and had the same issue, but first go on the cleanup day just overpowered it and it felt easy. Whatever it's a cool climb, I just wish it hadn't been messed with.
Took a while to figure out how to avoid dabbing. Wanted to try to flash the big 4 but quickly realizing that's literally impossible.
No jump cuz the driveby looked cool.
Easier than the other 7Cs, but not sure if a full grade easier. sick high heel hook on perfect slopers!
Kinda scary but really rad!
Questionable but everything else here is hard so w/e
Finished em up. Well I guess there's 5 now so I gotta come back for that other one. Took forever to figure out beta gotta start researching. Ended up with a wild sequence with overhead heel toe cam.
Took me longer than expected. Prob going to be my least favorite of these ones.
Not too hard, that crux move on berezina is still weird tho
WHaaaat so good. Took a while to figure out I was aiming for the wrong hold, but then bagged it. Thanks for pointing that out Elliot! 2 down.
Weird tweaky heel hook. Avoided all the big holds out right
Not too hard. Just gotta do abbatoir and apotheose sit now to finish the boulder.
One of the harder ones on here for me. Almost done with this boulder.
Fastest I've done anything here. Just another super fun boulder...
2 Sessions. Perfect boulder my favorite kind of climbing (not to  be confused with what I'm good at). Avoided the chipped hold of course.
Harder than almost everything else on this boulder. Lets gooooo
Took a while. Gonna have to be tall or have massive hops for this.

Feeling cute may dg later. Don't have enough to go off of here yet, we'll see after I try some more 8s. Super psyched to bag this thing, incredible line I've always heard so much about. Did it in about an hour.
Awesome, really wanted to do this one. Felt similar to karma, took an hour or two. Maybe  I'll be back...
Pretty cool for an eliminant. Glad I got out today, even if just for the mods.
Really good and aesthetic. What a beaut!
Nootz flew the flash. Cool elevator door move! How the eff do you do this if you aren't tall.
Classic in so many ways.
Brutal. Somehow made it up this. Being tall recommended.
Good times! Lei will bag the full line next time.
One of the harder mantles I've done...
Took a while. Not very aesthetic but very fun!
Hardest flash in Font to date. Really cool sequence on this one.
Went full epic on this one, almost died dry firing off the lip.
Sick line! Took a while to figure out I was going the wrong way. That's a really high heel hook.
Fun movement, forced it the way I knew I could but probably should have done it a better way.
Closest I've come to flashing a double d here must be a mega softy.
Few tries. Had to refine the lower sequence to keep chalk on my hands.
Easiest of the 5? Also when did they add this I thought I was done.
When you get one day of climbing after 2 rainy days before 2 rainy days really nothing is off limits.
Chalk really disappears off my hands quickly these days. Still did it quick, why is 8a+ easier than 7C+ here.
Nice one with a cool sloper. Bit contrived tho.
This might be the first problem in font that actually felt really really easy.
Not too hard but adds enough when the stand is so dicey.
1st go. fun!
So humid and moist today hardest thing I could claw up. Topout is scary this contrived way.
ascents.zlaggableName: Cent pofs et sans reproche direct

ascents.comment: YES don't know why but this is the one that spoke to me when I got to Font. And of course it ended up being mega for me, 4 sessions fell off of nearly every move multiple times, but finally the 5th session first go it felt so easy. Just had to dial everything in and execute, on these holds the clock is really ticking. The one I would have been really bummed to leave without.
Pretty sick one. Kinda hard for a warm up...
Felt very easy. Sup Ondra.

Spent the first half of the day unsuccessfully working on logistics for my rental car, spent the second half going to two areas with moist boulders to no avail. Finally bailed to my go to backup Rempart around 6PM. Came to this looking for a workout, all I left with was 12 easy points.
Same difficulty as atresie, so pretty darn soft. I wish it would stop being so humid water is just appearing out of thin air on everything.
Thought it was impossible but actually it's just soft. Just had to bump left hand. Topout is a bit spicy... 2 new problems in Joe's in a day? Unheard of.
ascents.cragName: Brenda boulder, just past Dairy Canyon

ascents.comment: Not ideal conditions in the sun but still went cuz it's soft. Exited naturally, contrived exit looks cool too but not like a different boulder at all. My 200th 8a?

Big moment for me, conquering the nemesis. 7th session nbd pretty sure it's low end for the grade. Tried incredibly hard, and forced it out. My proudest send of the year undoubtedly. Can't wait to see what the future has in store for me now.

Very soft but I'll take it. Top is still pretty scary due to the rapidly decreasing rock quality the higher you go. Super fun moves, super fun problem. Thanks to Dor Tim and Jess for hiking up the hill to get me on this thing!
Shame on me. Shoulda warmed up a little more. Fun times dicking around with T Chen Jesse and Bryce.
Felt hard climbing it head on, did it again after with a kneepad and it was laughably easy for v9. But hey do it however you want to.
Felt really hard for 7 but then Will broke it and I first go softed the new line. Still goes, prob a little harder.
Sweaty boy hands made for unpleasant crimpings but committed to shredding my skin 2nd try today and bagged it.

This is the bouldering experience I'm always looking for! V8 is such a magical grade in the valley, hard enough to feel worthwhile and in this case tall enough to be scary. Required a few breakthroughs and drop offs, awesome movement. Man I love climbing here.

Bad problem. Managed to create my own reachy boy sequence, from the good right hand downpull crystal pocket left heel on the start hold then bump 3 times over the lip left, jump to the jug. Thanks Tim for climbing on this with me would have given up on this pile ages ago.Turns out even after 8 months fat boy can still crimp
easy and bad.
Cool line, blew the flash numbing out on the sit. way to go tim! fun mid afternoon sesh

Got the 1 2 with T chen using Andy's beta. Too bad he had to drop out of the race due to skin issues, it was just getting exciting... start on the obvious big holds to the right. Thanks for letting us have this one Purdy!
I second it is not. And I'm heavy.
Bagged it at the end of the day, had to force the Mossman
Impossible in 70 degrees but pretty manageable 20-30 degrees colder.
Hard for me. Can't believe this is supposed to be easier than treebeard. Cool holds!
Took more goes today than halfway... harder than I was expecting. Or scarier I guess. super fun!
So much easier than Mossman. Lots of new boulders today!
Reachy and dumb. Harder than public execution for what that's worth. Wow just back in the game and double doubling on the best boulders out here
Not quite off the couch but pretty close. Guess I've still got my flashing abilities, if nothing else. Cooler than I thought it would be, almost pumped off the end.

Cooler than I thought, and easier too. Fits my size rather well, managed to do the whole thing more or less static which is good because I have forgotten how to rock climb and deadpoint coordination is not what it used to be.
What is next!?
Super fun. Steven with the hail mary dragonfly send was rad.
Fun day following the crew around.
From a sit start, with a kneepad. Softy send train with C Barth

Outdoor climbing is painful and hard, especially when you're overweight and out of shape. Tried a long while back several days on, felt very hard until I did it, then everything clicked and it wasn't so bad.
Got to hang with Marc and Ash again it's been a while. Getting ready for wheel of Chupa
3 tries starting at 5:30. Just gotta crimp hard and suffer
Handful of tries. Prob not V12
Bit confusing but not bad once you find the right sequence.
Pure line. Not the best or most comfortable.
Great climb. Bit of a dab at the top. Forgot how to flash.
Poopa Scoopa

Didn't mantle, chucked out left. Didn't realize the mantle was an option...
Nice one bro
Fun minus the footless section initially. Topout is wierd and three dimensional. Fun with the crew for the Bach weekend!
Flash train with Bryce. Reversed the running order and it worked! Good to be back out.
Fun height dependent compy problem. Sick send from Bryce!
So good
Bunchy grainy underclings in 80 degrees. Brutal for me. At least it sucks
Tricky topout
Didn't know there were good problems at Rainbow. This is where they're all hiding!
Remembered this being scary but it's kinda fine. Crazy moves
Start hold is unpleasant. Shoulder to underclings with no feet.
Not the best warmup but let's be real people this thing is not very hard
Good style for me. Fun problem, 30 min or so.
Awkward. at least it's all natty. felt like the good old days being out with Tim
I guess this is a climb. Harder than moulin... but that last move is way more fun! Way to go Nic on deja
